PARTIAL_DARKNESS
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are in a huge room that has a lot of things in it, but has space to
live in as well. There a neatly packed study area, one for mechanical
experiments as well as a trio of seperated beds.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 1 1226 VAL2=463 ; Dungeon
ITEM 2 946 VAL2=464  ; Here there be mages
ITEM 3 60 VAL2=465   ; Mechs be crazy
ITEM 4 73 VAL2=466   ; Highlanders Homes

IFPREVERB GO 3
  IFVAR TRAPDEACT = 0
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER As you go to walk through the arch, a giant polearm swings from a hidden recess in the wall and knocks you against the far wall.
    ECHO OTHERS You watch as %n is flung back against the far wall by a large polearm that swings out of nowhere.
    DISBAND
    POSITION LAY
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SEARCH 3
  IFVAR TRAPDEACT = 0
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You examine the arch carefully, and notice a barely-visible trip-wire and deactivate it.
    ECHO OTHERS %n examins the arch carefully, and bends over to fiddle with something.
    EQUAL TRAPDEACT 1
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You notice that a trip-wire has already been deactivated.
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY HAIL_BROTHER!
  IFVAR STURMTALON = 0
    EQUAL STURMTALON 1
    ECHO ALL You hear a voice from the other room, "Farewell, bother."
    ECHO ALL You see the back of a giant talon lift up to reveal an opening.
    NEWITEM 9 72 VAL2=759
    AFFECT 759
    ECHO ALL The statue animates for a moment, lifting a giant talon to reveal an opening.
    NEWITEM 9 72 VAL2=440
    AFFECT 440
  ELSE
    ECHO ALL The statue turns it head and says, "Hail brother!"
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY GUARD_THE_WAY
  IFVAR STURMTALON = 1
    EQUAL STURMTALON 0
    ECHO ALL You hear a voice from the other room saying, "Always have I guarded you and yours."
    ECHO ALL You see the back of a giant talon lowering to the floor, blocking an opening.
    REMOVEITEM 9
    AFFECT 759
    REMOVEITEM 9
    ECHO ALL The statue animates for a moment, lowering its talon blocking an opening.
    AFFECT 440
  ELSE
    ECHO ALL The statue turns it head and says, "Always have I guarded you and yours."
  ENDIF
ENDIF

NUMBER 463
NAME Dungeon
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
After descending a long flight of stairs, you come to what can only be a
place used to house other living beings. It is kept quite clean and there
is no sign of the rats one would expect in a room like this. Though there
is no sign of recent use, all the items for extracting information are
visible and ready to be used. Though the room is vast, there is only one
holding cell for prisoners which is sealed off from this room by a iron
door with a small window.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 1 943 ADJ1=1289 ADJ2=169 VAL1=300 VAL2=467 VAL3=467 CLOSED LOCKED ; Cell #1
ITEM 2 249 ADJ1=294
ITEM 3 81 VAL2=440

EXTEND 2 with iron bars through the center

IFPREVERB LOOK 2
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You bend over and look through the small window in the door...
  ECHO OTHERS %N bends over to look throught the small window in the door.
  SHOWROOM 467
ENDIF

NUMBER 467
NAME Holding Cell #1
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
This room contains one long bench which is part of the wall. It can be
used for both sitting and a bed. There is a banded iron door with a small
window set into it. There appears to be no keyhole on this side.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 1 946 ADJ1=1289 ADJ2=169 VAL2=463 VAL3=758 OPEN  ; Dungeon

IFVERB LISTEN -1
  RANDOM DUMMY1 1 4 0
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER %cYou hear a voice whisper to you, "Have you been bad?"
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 2
    ECHO PLAYER %cYou hear a voice whisper to you, "You must have done something very wrong."
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 3
    ECHO PLAYER %cYou hear a voice whisper to you, "Most criminals end up in rooms just like this one."
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 4
    ECHO PLAYER %cYou hear a voice whisper to you, "Where's the cheese?"
  ENDIF
ENDIF

NUMBER 464
NAME Here There Be Mages
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
This room is the definition of "cluttered". Scrolls and Books lay about on
tables and the floor in no order dealing with every subject from "Grass:
Our Friend" to "Altering the Time Space Continuum". Arranged on a vast
table are an assortment of spell components and gems with very detailed
directions on how each is to be used....and NOT used. Along one wall is a
large four- poster bed. Spaced evenly about the room are three sconces in
the shape of a dragon.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 1 946 VAL2=440
ITEM 2 1311
ITEM 3 1311
ITEM 4 1311

IFENTRY -1
  ECHO ALL A ghostly sheep appears and bleets "Whaaats the paaaaassss wooorrd?"
ENDIF

IFSAY NONE_OF_YOUR_DAMN_BUSINESS.
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
    EQUAL FLAG1 1
    ECHO ALL The ghostly sheep turns tail and ducks under the bed.
  ENDIF
ELSE
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
    ECHO ALL A ghostly sheep bleets, "Wrooooooonnnnng!"
    ECHO PLAYER The ghostly sheep then boots you out of the room!
    ECHO OTHERS The ghostly sheep then boots %n out of the room.
    MOVE 440
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFTOUCH -1
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
    ECHO ALL A ghostly sheep kicks you the hell out of the room.
    MOVE 440
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY LIGHT.
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
    ECHO ALL %cThree sconces along the walls of the room suddenly light up.
    LIGHT 2
    LIGHT 3
    LIGHT 4
  ELSE
    ECHO ALL A ghostly sheep kicks you out of the room.
    MOVE 440
  ENDIF
ENDIF

NUMBER 465
NAME Mechs Be Crazy
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
Upon entering this room, your eyes are immediately drawn to a strange
looking rectangular box with a humanoid shaped impression. Many tubes and
wires run to this contraption ending at small junctions within the human
mold. There is a strong smell of ozone in this place and none of the
things a living creature would use to make the room comfortable. Obviously
this room belongs to a being made from ancient technology. There's even a
complete tool box next to the strange contraption for quick tune-ups.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 1 60 VAL2=440
ITEM 2 247

IFVERB GO 1
  EQUAL TRAPDEACT 0
  ECHO PLAYER %cAs you walk through the arch, you can hear a faint mechanical "click".
ENDIF

IFVERB SEARCH -1
  IFVAR STURMSEARCH = 0
    ECHO PLAYER %cYou find a hidden button.
    EQUAL STURMSEARCH 1
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER %cYou see a button.
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVERB PUSH 4
  ECHO ALL %cStrange light fills the room for a moment.
ENDIF

NUMBER 466
NAME Highlander Home
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
Upon emerging from the passageway, you enter a small, but comfortable cave
that has obviously been carved out by an expert. Each stone slab is
perfectly symmetrical with all the others and there appears to be no gap
between one stone to the next. In one corner is a bed which is also of
carved stone. Also in the room are a stone chair and a stone table. Upon
closer examination, you notice many polished gems imbedded into all the
furniture and walls which reflect and magnify the light coming from a
source beyond the walls themselves!
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 1 73 VAL2=440
